 Mpumalanga achieved a 79% overall pass rate, while Steve Tshwete Circuit 3 scooped the number one spot in the province. Hosting a breakfast in Aerorand to honour the top achievers, Mayor Tolo spoke about the importance of preparing learners for the Fourth Industrial Revolution, he also urged the achievers to return to the town after their studies. Johnathan Mtshweni, a former Mphanama Secondary School learner, told the honourees to not lose focus at university. Laurike Erasmus of Hoër Tegniese Skool Middelburg was named the top matric achiever in the municipality, followed by Sabiha Patel in second position. Naledi Masehla of Mphanama Secondary School received third place. Colin Tonga, Laurike Erasmus of Hoër Tegniese Skool Middelburg and Mayor Bagudi Tolo. Top achievers with Mayor Bagudi Tolo.   Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za